content: When we get an answering machine are we to be leaving messages?
no messages!
how about staying on script? is that "best practice" with the best way to reach them? or is it up to us ...if we can get the questions answered and move along the script process

Make it your own as long as you answer the survey questions and hit the bolded issues (as far as you can take them).  Only thing you must say for legal reasons is you are calling from the Harris - Walz campaign (or the Democrats).

perfect. I did that on all calls so far. I'll work on a lil intro and get familiar with the script. day one was a lil rough ..but i'm on the phones all day in Healthcare for insurance/medicaid/medicare so if I practice I'll get better.  ..no way to watch our count right? I was going for 50
a lot of our callers keep a little tick sheet to track.  Sounds like you are off to a great start.  The scripts can be a little much so making it your own is great!
i'll do my best! ok thanks for the info! i'm looking at the preview script and some good links and numbers ..so I'll make myself a lil cheat sheet and try again tomorrow.
Just wanted to pop in and say <a:ThanksRainbow:1278765693579431967> for being here and helping out! You rock!
noo thank YOU GUYS for making this happen. I appreciate it.
I just noticed your profile name.  Are you from Denver?
i'm from Santa Fe, NM ..but been dwntwn by coors field for like 23yrs
does [CO] mean Colorado?

I am from Denver.  I thought it was important for me to help from our amazing blue state.  You can drop into the calls team any day 9am-11:30pm ET and we'll get you on the dialer and tell you who we are talking to.
oh very cool. ok i'll start calling as much as possilbe these last days
Yep!
19 days to go.  Let's GOOOOO!
on it!! (...studying tonight but I dove in and gave it a shot! trying to get more w/ me to make some calls. : )
i speak spanish ...do i just translate what's being asked if I get a spanish speaker? or is there a way to dial that demographic?
Changed the channel name: Various Questions "day 1"
Yes if you speak Spanish you can continue the call and answer the survey responses.  We do have specific Spanish Speaking zoom phone banks too https://events.democrats.org/event/647512/.
perfect! thank you!!
We are calling Michigan this morning if you want to join us. ðŸŒŠ
I've been on the phone all day for Medicaid/Medicare for our Care Management Program with Anthem BCBS ...buttt now I'm making some calls! : )) ............question:

I'm getting to: the voter part of the questionere but the call is disconnected. (in this situation ...he said he just got a call like this 5 min ago ...and I was going to help him not receive another call ...but he didn't stay on the line with me long enough to get through the questions ..about voting) ....shall I back out and log it so he won't get another call? ...or what's best?
Glad to have you back, we are calling Georgia.
I'mGA Medicaid out there lol
hang up is probably the best response for that one
hang up? ok TY!!
Also, FYI, if people say they've gotten multiple calls that same day, let them know that *many* organizations are calling about the election
that's true. I will definitely say that
whew! this is rough! but did 30min so far
Hop into <#1242256751445934262> Megan Morris just posted her 2 hr stats (she tracks herself)

very cool. i'll go find that ..this might be my first time on discord ...so getting familiar.    .................I just got a "strong supporter" for Harris ...he disconnected at the voting part of the script.  ....so i "back out" and click hang up? or..
you can end the survey after the strong harris entry
perfect! ok i'll do it like that ...that makes more sense now
its gets a little chatty over there sometimes but its inspiring to see who else is on the dialer with you.
Are the numbers being called cell phones, land lines, or some of both?
you will reach both
Is the intent to randomly contact voters regardless of any intel on their politics?
Asking because canvasers in my neoghborhood already know my voter registration and they avoid registered Rs.

no, for the most part we are calling cultivated lists based on voter behavior.  Tonight we are calling into GA to ask voting intentions and ask about their voting plans.  We'll reach all parties though.
OK - cool. Thanks. And one more question; does this work? I mean, does it really make a difference?
I ask because I've never been called.

visit the <#1242256751445934262> channel where you can see comments from those currently on our dialer.  <@1283417540244275311> is one of our phone bank facilitators.  Can you tell Mike the stat about voters who speak with phone banks?
thanks <@112080668296564736> I knew someone had it close by!
OK! Thanks - I'll. get started ASAP.
I was just looking at the new deck and thought I'd share ðŸ˜„
Here is the link to our dialer if you'd like to get a preview first https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5FYlZK0essc
that's what I was lookin' for! it's helpful to see ....what's workin'!  ...day 2 ...getting better.
there is a text traning today. i was going to try that too!  <#1266829704204386334>
